Scripts to generates a daily digest PDF in pocketmod booklet form to print out and enjoy.

See: http://www.pocketmod.com/

There's not much to it yet, I'm slowly filling in the pages of the booklet. I'll add them here in the order they appear:

1. Last.fm event recommendations
2. Tube line and station status
3. Twitter updates
4. Newsgator RSS headlines
5. 
6. 
7. 
8. 

Required libs:
- pylast 0.3 branch (slightly modified â€” ask for details): http://code.google.com/p/pylast/
- ReportLab: http://www.reportlab.org/
- simplejson: http://code.google.com/p/simplejson/
- BeautifulSoup: http://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/
- feedparser: http://www.feedparser.org/

You'll also need a settings module which defines these globals:
GMAPS_KEY
LASTFM_KEY
LASTFM_SECRET
LASTFM_SESSION
TWITTER_USERNAME
TWITTER_PASSWORD
TWITTER_USERID
NEWSGATOR_KEY
NEWSGATOR_USERNAME
NEWSGATOR_PASSWORD
NEWSGATOR_LOCATIONID

APIs:
- Google Static Maps: http://code.google.com/apis/maps/documentation/staticmaps/
- Last.fm: http://www.last.fm/api
- Twitter: http://apiwiki.twitter.com/
- Newsgator: http://www.newsgator.com/ngs/api/

Screen Scraping:
- TFL: http://www.tfl.gov.uk/